  <title translate="true">SUnit Resource Browser Tool</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Popup Heading"><text styleclass="Popup Heading" translate="true">SUnit Resource Browser Tool</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Popup Heading"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:middle; width:99px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Heading"><image src="SUnit Resource Browser.png" align="left" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:middle; width:214px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Opens the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">SUnit Resource Browser</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> which allows you to manage the resources associated with some SUnit tests.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">In this context a resource can be described as something required by a group of unit tests that typically takes a relatively long time to set up and initialise. The</text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">SUnit Resource Browser</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> allows you to start and stop resources once, before and after a group of tests are run. This saves executing the lengthy setup (and possibly tear down) phases for every test.</text></para>
  </body>
